    "base_path":  "/guidance/apply-for-the-covid-19-corporate-financing-facility",
    "content_id":  "0834f258-9af1-46f4-a51c-9e69c38ccd7c",
    "description":  "This scheme helps large businesses affected by coronavirus (COVID-19) through the purchase of their short-term debt.",
    "details":  {
                    "attachments":  [

                                    ],
                    "body":  "\u003cdiv class=\"govspeak\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eUnder the \u003cabbr title=\"coronavirus\"\u003eCOVID-19\u003c/abbr\u003e Corporate Financing Facility (\u003cabbr title=\"COVID-19 Corporate Financing Facility\"\u003eCCFF\u003c/abbr\u003e), the Bank of England will buy short-term debt from large companies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis scheme will support your company if it’s been affected by a short-term funding squeeze, and allow you to finance your short-term liabilities.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt will also support corporate finance markets overall and ease the supply of credit to all firms.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe scheme is delivered through commercial lenders, backed by the Bank of England. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIt will operate for at least 12 months, and for as long as steps are needed to relieve cash flow pressures on firms that make a material contribution to the UK economy.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"eligibility\"\u003eEligibility\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCompanies – and their finance subsidiaries – that make a material contribution to the UK economy are able to participate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.bankofengland.co.uk/news/2020/march/the-covid-corporate-financing-facility\" class=\"govuk-link\"\u003eCheck your eligibility on the Bank of England website\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"how-to-apply\"\u003eHow to apply\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eApplications closed on 31 December 2020.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e",
